    "harder_than_needed": "The story brief flagged the `getChakraTheme` signature as an open structural question (the seam contract's stated form is `getChakraTheme(id) = extendTheme(buildThemeOverride(APP_THEMES[id]))`, which requires a registry that does not exist until S2). Resolving this without escalating required cross-referencing architecture.md's terse 'Allowed dependency edges' list (buildChakraTheme -> @chakra-ui/react, treatments/* only, no registry edge) against Chakra's own exported `ThemeOverride`/`extendTheme` type definitions (checked directly in node_modules) to confirm a manifest-keyed `getChakraTheme(manifest)` both type-checks cleanly and composes correctly once index.ts wires in the registry in S2. This took real investigation time but resolved cleanly; documented as a design note in architecture.json and as post-impl question VQ-S1-011 for the verifier to confirm.",
